cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for semi-supervised feature learning that utilizes both manifold structure and local discriminant information. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and computer vision, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of labels to minimize distances between data from the same class, which could also relate to natural language processing and text classification, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) another possible sub-category.
